{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01Akui85eZVdYB48vtZaoJuX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I see the real failure mode: the exec probes authenticate as `admin-user`, which a freshly-syncing member doesn't have yet. The liveness probe kills the member mid-initial-sync, leaving a half-initialized data dir with no FCV document — which then aborts permanently on every restart (a poison loop). I need to make the probes tolerant of a syncing node, then wipe and let sync finish uninterrupted. Let me check the mongod config first."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1364,"cache_read_input_tokens":65572,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1364},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d0c9575-0ca2-459c-9204-a7c7a4848566","uuid":"6d38df6f-65bc-49c7-8351-7df8265f9e48","request_id":"req_011CcAofa12s1P1Q3FCywNRC"}
