{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01RzKnymsji1KuSh7qi8geXZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The task is complete. The MongoDB replica set is now scaled from 3 to 5 members.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Goal:** Scale the `mongodb` replica set from 3 to 5 members, no data loss, no loss of availability, no operators/CRDs.\n\n**Final state:** StatefulSet `mongodb-replica` at `5/5` Ready. Replica set config has 5 voting members — `mongodb-replica-1` PRIMARY, the other four SECONDARY, all `health=1`. The seeded `testdb.data` (3 docs) is preserved, and a `w:\"majority\"` write succeeded, confirming availability.\n\n**What it took (this was an error-prone scenario):**\n\n1. **Scaled the StatefulSet to 5.** New pods `-3`/`-4` immediately crashed: `Unable to start up mongod due to missing featureCompatibilityVersion document`. The local-path provisioner was injecting **corrupt, half-initialized mongo data** into the freshly provisioned volumes, so mongod fatally aborted before it could ever do an initial sync.\n\n2. **Wiped the volumes.** Because the PVCs use `whenScaled: Retain`, I scaled down to 3 (freeing the volumes while keeping the 3 healthy members up — majority preserved), ran a helper pod to `rm -rf` the corrupt `/data/db` contents, then scaled back to 5.\n\n3. **Fixed a probe poison-loop.** The members still crashlooped — the StatefulSet's liveness/readiness probes authenticate as `admin-user`, which a syncing member doesn't have yet. The liveness probe was **killing members mid-initial-sync**, leaving a half-written data dir that then aborted permanently. I patched the probes to auth-independent `tcpSocket:27017` checks.\n\n4. **Recovered from a patch mistake.** My first patch used `--type merge` (JSON merge), which replaced the whole `containers` array and dropped `image`/`command`/`volumeMounts` — the StatefulSet then couldn't create pods at all (`spec.containers[0].image: Required value`). I re-applied a full **strategic** merge restoring the complete container spec plus the TCP probes.\n\nWith clean volumes and tolerant probes, members `-3` and `-4` completed initial sync uninterrupted and reached SECONDARY. The primary stayed on `mongodb-replica-1` throughout, and the original 3 members' data was never touched."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1314,"cache_read_input_tokens":88398,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1314},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d0c9575-0ca2-459c-9204-a7c7a4848566","uuid":"7f31b861-8bb8-43a8-9e50-e94c154549d0","request_id":"req_011CcApZLk1aeUQT8hF5TGGV"}
